<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-elPesoDeLasMascotas" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>El peso de las mascotas</title>

<statement>
  <p>Empareja cada mascota con la cantidad que podría ser su peso. Explica cómo razonaste.</p>
  <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%">
    <sidebyside>
      <p>mascota</p>
      <p>peso</p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
      <stack>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>conejillo de indias</p>
            <image source="png-source/Guinea Pig.png">
              <shortdescription>conejillo de indias</shortdescription>
            </image>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>perro</p>
            <image source="png-source/Dog.png">
              <shortdescription>perro</shortdescription>
            </image>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>pez pequeño</p>
            <image source="png-source/Small Fish.png">
              <shortdescription>pez pequeño</shortdescription>
            </image>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>gato</p>
            <image source="png-source/Cat.png">
              <shortdescription>gato</shortdescription>
            </image>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </stack>
      <stack>
        <ol marker="A.">
          <li>
            <p>20 kilogramos</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>1 kilogramo</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>3 kilogramos</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>3 gramos</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </stack>
    </sidebyside>
  </sbsgroup>
    
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>1. B, 2. A, 3. D, 4. C</p>
  </solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-MD-A-2" text="custom">3.MD.A.2</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to use what they’ve learned about grams and kilograms to estimate the weights of some common pets. Students should rely on the experiences they have had in previous activities to explain why the estimates they choose are reasonable. In the synthesis, students consider when it might be helpful to estimate a weight rather than measure the exact weight.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Con su compañero, emparejen cada mascota con una cantidad que podría ser su peso</q>
      </li>
      <li>3–5 minutes: partner work time</li>
      <li>Monitor for students who refer back to the activities where they felt different weights to determine a reasonable estimate of each pet’s weight.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Estrategias de apoyo para estudiantes con dificultades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="support-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>If students choose estimates for the weight of the pets that aren’t reasonable, consider asking:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Cuéntame cómo estimaste el peso de la mascota</q>
      </li>
      <li>
        <q>¿La mascota pesa más que o menos que un gramo (o un kilogramo)?</q>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Invite 3-4 students to share their response for one of the pets, including how they determined the amount would be a reasonable estimate.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Descripción del desarrollo de lenguaje matemático -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="language-actividad-titulo"/></title><p>[++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p><em>MLR8 Discussion Supports.</em> Synthesis: Before students share, remind students to use words such as weight, grams, and kilograms.</p>
    <p>
      <em>Advances: Speaking</em>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Estrategias de acceso para estudiantes con discapacidades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="accesibility-actividad-titulo"/></title><p>[++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p><em>Action and Expression: Develop Expression and Communication.</em> Provide access to the weights used in the previous activity to determine a reasonable weight for each pet.</p>
    <p>
      <em>Supports accessibility for: Conceptual Processing</em>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

</activity>